{"id":45358,"title":"A bleeding esophagopulmonary fistula: rare complication of stasis ulcer in refractory achalasia.","abstract":"Achalasia refractory to Heller cardiomyotomy is a rare problem. Complications arising from long-standing achalasia include perforation because of stasis ulcers and malignancy. Here, we report a case of refractory achalasia presenting with recurrent hematemesis because of a perforated stasis ulcer leading to a bleeding esophagopulmonary fistula. ","date":"2014-04-01","categories":"Digestive System Diseases","split":"test","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24686369","annotations":[{"name":"Fistula","weight":0.818674,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fistula"},{"name":"Bleeding","weight":0.723286,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bleeding"},{"name":"Peptic ulcer","weight":0.720725,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peptic_ulcer"},{"name":"Malignancy","weight":0.700396,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Malignancy"},{"name":"Hematemesis","weight":0.563317,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hematemesis"},{"name":"Complication (medicine)","weight":0.18053,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Complication_(medicine)"},{"name":"Perforation","weight":0.123431,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Perforation"},{"name":"Achalasia","weight":0.116968,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Achalasia"},{"name":"Refractory","weight":0.0137481,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Refractory"}]}
